flowwing below commands 
URL= https://www.fosstechnix.com/how-to-install-mysql-5-7-on-ubuntu-20-04-lts/

a) Step #1: Add MySQL APT Repository in Ubuntu
> sudo apt update
b)Install wget on ubuntu if not installed
> sudo apt install wget -y
c) Below are commands to add/download latest MySQL APT repository using command line,
>   wget https://dev.mysql.com/get/mysql-apt-config_0.8.12-1_all.debCopied!
d) then, below command is to install above downloaded apt repository,
> sudo dpkg -i mysql-apt-config_0.8.12-1_all.deb
e) Update apt repository
> sudo apt-get update
f) now install mysql 5.7 
> sudo apt-get install mysql-server 
>  mysql_secure_installation

